title: Advance PDF Password Removal (Ver 1.48)
description:
This is an older version (1.48) of the program, I was reading that some people were having problems with the new versions and were looking for the older ones, which no longer seem available. 

This is an .exe file, open the file, (there is no program install) click on the icon in the upper left to navigate back to where the locked pdf is. 

If the file is encrypted it will strip it away, if it isn&#039;t, it will tell you so.

Remember to save a copy of the newly unlocked pdf before you close it out.

Webwasher-Gateway reports      Win32.Malware.gen (suspicious)


This program (Advanced PDF Password Recovery, or APDFPR) is intended to decrypt password-protected and restricted Adobe Acrobat PDF files, which have "user" password set (required to open/view the file), and/or "owner" password (when the file is only protected from editing, printing etc), i.e. remove the protection and/or break the PDF password. Restricted files are being unprotected instantly, while decryption of files with "open" password may be time-consuming. The program is also able to convert Kinko&#039;s Document Format (KDF) files to PDF files (without any protection).

I swiped this program description, in part, from uploader Crazy.Sexy.Dirty.Money here: http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/4156525/Advanced_PDF_Password_Recovery_Professional_3.10
